export const sourceCode = "# Visual Inspector\n\nThe inspector lets you see exactly which element on the page has an accessibility issue.\n\n## Opening the Inspector\n\nFrom any issue card, click **Inspect Element** to open the full-screen inspector overlay.\n\n## Two View Modes\n\n### Page View\n\nShows the captured screenshot with the problematic element highlighted:\n\n- **Red overlay** dims the rest of the page\n- **Colored highlight box** around the element (color matches severity)\n- **Label** shows severity + WCAG criterion\n- **Zoom controls** — zoom in/out (25%-200%), reset\n- **Bounding box coordinates** displayed at top\n\nThe inspector auto-scrolls to center the highlighted element.\n\n### HTML View\n\nShows the page's DOM source with syntax highlighting:\n\n- VS Code-style colors (tags cyan, attributes magenta, values green)\n- The problematic element's line is highlighted\n- Line numbers in the gutter\n- Windowed rendering (loads lines around the match for performance)\n- \"Show more lines\" buttons to expand context\n\n## Sidebar\n\nThe left sidebar shows:\n\n- **Issue title** and description\n- **Severity badge**, WCAG criterion, level, and type\n- **\"Why is this an issue?\"** — expandable explanation\n- **Occurrences** — if multiple instances of the same rule, navigate between them\n- **Element HTML** — code snippet with copy button\n- **Selector** — CSS selector with copy button\n- **Fix suggestion** — amber-highlighted remediation steps\n\n## Keyboard Shortcuts\n\n- **Escape** — close inspector\n- **Arrow Up/Down** — navigate between occurrences of the same rule";
