export const sourceCode = "# Full Site Crawl\n\nCrawl an entire website, scanning every discovered page for accessibility violations.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **Discovery** — BFS crawl follows internal links + parses sitemap.xml\n2. **Concurrent scanning** — Up to 3 pages scanned simultaneously\n3. **AI enrichment** — Up to 2 parallel enrichment calls\n4. **Finalization** — Aggregate scores, compute issue diff vs previous crawl\n\n## Starting a Crawl\n\n### From the UI\n\n1. Open the Dashboard\n2. Your site appears in the sidebar (auto-created on first scan)\n3. Click into the site → **Crawl Now**\n4. Watch live progress as pages are discovered and scanned\n\n### From the API\n\n```bash\n# Create a site (or get existing)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/sites \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"url\": \"https://example.com\"}'\n\n# Start a crawl\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/sites/{siteId}/crawl\n\n# Optionally limit pages\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/sites/{siteId}/crawl \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"maxPages\": 20}'\n```\n\n## Discovery\n\nThe crawler uses lightweight HTTP fetch (not Playwright) for fast page discovery:\n\n- Follows `<a href>`, `<link href>`, `<iframe src>` tags\n- Parses `/sitemap.xml` for additional URLs\n- Same-origin filter — only crawls pages on the same domain\n- URL normalization — deduplicates trailing slashes, fragments, tracking params\n- Configurable delay between fetches (`CRAWL_DELAY_MS`, default 200ms)\n\n## Concurrency\n\nThree BullMQ queues handle the work:\n\n| Queue | Concurrency | Purpose |\n|-------|------------|---------|\n| `crawl-discovery` | 1 | BFS link discovery |\n| `page-scan` | 3 (configurable) | Playwright + axe-core per page |\n| `ai-enrichment` | 2 (configurable) | LLM enrichment per page |\n\nConfigure via environment variables:\n- `WORKER_CONCURRENCY` — parallel Playwright instances (default 3)\n- `AI_CONCURRENCY` — parallel LLM calls (default 2)\n- `MAX_CRAWL_PAGES` — hard page cap (empty = unlimited)\n\n## Crawl Lifecycle\n\n```\nqueued → discovering → scanning → completed\n                                → failed\n                                → cancelled\n```\n\n- Only one crawl can run per site at a time\n- Cancel anytime via the UI or `POST /api/sites/{siteId}/crawls/{crawlId}/cancel`\n\n## Limitations\n\n- Discovery uses plain HTTP fetch — JavaScript-rendered SPAs may yield fewer discovered links\n- `robots.txt` is not respected (by design)\n- No authentication support for protected pages (yet)";
