export const sourceCode = "# FAQ\n\n## General\n\n### What is ClearSight?\n\nClearSight is an open-source accessibility checker that scans websites for WCAG 2.1 Level A and AA violations. It uses axe-core for detection, custom engines for link text and touch targets, and AI (Azure OpenAI) for enriched descriptions and fix suggestions.\n\n### Is ClearSight free?\n\nYes. ClearSight is open-source. You need to provide your own Azure OpenAI API key for AI enrichment. Without it, scans still work but produce basic (non-AI) descriptions.\n\n## Scanning\n\n### How long does a scan take?\n\nA single page typically takes 30-60 seconds. A full site crawl depends on the number of pages — with 3 concurrent scanners, expect ~20 seconds per page after discovery.\n\n### Can I scan sites behind authentication?\n\nNot yet. ClearSight currently only scans publicly accessible pages.\n\n### Does ClearSight respect robots.txt?\n\nNo. ClearSight does not check robots.txt. It scans all same-origin pages it discovers.\n\n### What if AI enrichment fails?\n\nScans fall back to basic descriptions from axe-core rule help text. The scan completes with a `completed_partial` status. You still get all issues — just without AI-enhanced descriptions.\n\n## Results\n\n### What's the difference between confirmed and potential issues?\n\n**Confirmed** issues are definite WCAG violations (e.g., missing alt text). **Potential** issues need human review — the tool suspects a problem but can't be certain.\n\n### How is the score calculated?\n\nAI analyzes the type, severity, and count of issues to produce a 0-100 score. If AI is unavailable, a simple heuristic subtracts 5 points per issue from 100.\n\n### Can I dismiss false positives?\n\nYes. From the Issues view, click **Dismiss** on any issue. Dismissed issues stay hidden across future crawls until you reopen them.\n\n## Technical\n\n### What browsers does ClearSight use?\n\nHeadless Chromium via Playwright, running at 1280x720 viewport.\n\n### What WCAG rules are checked?\n\n50+ rules from axe-core covering WCAG 2.1 Level A and AA, plus custom engines for link text quality and touch target sizing (48x48px minimum).\n\n### Can I run ClearSight locally?\n\nYes. Run `pnpm docker:dev` to start all services (PostgreSQL, Redis, Next.js app, worker, Bull Board) with Docker Compose.";
